ument section titled \"PREMIUM PERSONALIZATION PRICING STRATEGY - UPDATED\" for Family Gift Studio. Include the following sections with professional formatting: 1. **EXECUTIVE PRICING SUMMARY** - A bold statement highlighting the exceptional 52-103% premium margins achieved 2. **ACTUAL PRICING TABLE** with the following accurate data: - Jewelry Sets: Base $59 → Personalized $120 (103% increase, $61 premium) - Throw Blankets (50x60): Base $59 → Personalized $120 (103% increase, $61 premium) - Queen Blankets (80x90): Base $79 → Personalized $120 (52% increase, $41 premium) Table columns: Product Type | Base Price | Personalized Price | Premium Amount | % Increase | Annual Volume Est. | Revenue Impact 3. **ROI PROJECTION TABLE** showing: - Monthly sales projections (conservative, moderate, aggressive) - Average premium per personalized item - Total additional monthly revenue - Annual revenue impact - Profit margin improvement 4. **COMPETITIVE JUSTIFICATION** section explaining why these premiums are market-appropriate with data points 5. **PSYCHOLOGICAL PRICING TRIGGERS** explaining the $120 price anchor strategy 6. **IMPLEMENTATION TACTICS** - Step-by-step guide to rolling out premium pricing 7. **RISK MITIGATION** - How to handle price resistance Use professional color scheme: - Headers in dark blue (#1a365d) - Premium pricing in gold/green highlighting - Tables with alternating row colors - Warning boxes in soft yellow - Success metrics in light green Make it tactical, data-driven, and ready to implement. Include specific ROI calculations based on conservative estimates (20 personalized items/month to start). Excellent! Now let me view the complete document to ensure all sections are properly formatted, and then I'll create a summary document showing the key changes. Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 180,382 Perfect! The document is complete and professionally formatted. Now let me create a visual summary showing the updated pricing strategy comparisons: Using